WRITING.TITLE: Is it possible to lose 40kg in 12 weeks?
WRITING.TEXT: I've just started keto and IF (16:8) Current weight 115kg Target weight 75kg I have an event coming up in 12 weeks time, and would love to be 75kg by then. I also have an outfit picked out to wear. What is everyone's experience? Do you think it's possible to lose that much? A few friends are saying it's impossible to lose that much weight in 12 weeks. Perhaps they're right, but they've not tried keto. Also I'm of the opinion that aiming higher will help me stick to it. What do you guys think? What's your experiences? Any advice is welcomed
Thank you, I mean I'm not going to push it or do anything stupid. But a higher goal for me means I will stick to it rather than drop it after a week

It's just a target and target date for me to aim for. If I get there I get there. If I just lose some weight before that date but don't get to the target it's ok, I won't be disappointed as any weight lost is worth it. I can reassess as I get there.
Thanks! You've been helpful!! I've been calorie counting for a while, but have just been maintaining so anything lost is worthwhile. I'll see what happens whilst doing keto

I understand, for me higher goals and targets work. I'm bad for snacking and thinking it'll be ok I'll behave tomorrow. In this case I can't do that because I have a goal. I won't do anything unhealthy, as in the long term that will be more damaging to my health and could cause rebound weight gain! I mean I'll be happy if I hit 100kg by that date, I know it's not a race. I just have to focus on being relentless and getting out of bad habits. Thanks, I also have a backup outfit planned so either will look good!
I'm exactly the same as you. So maybe we will! I'll post back here and see what happens!!
Any weight loss for the event is going to be worth it, but I have to be strict on myself so a higher goal will keep me motivated and away from bad eating habits or just giving up all together.
Thank you, gives me numbers and figures to work with which suits my analytical mind

Well my goal is higher because it stops me from cheating. I know myself well. If my goal was 15kg in 3 months I would be "oh I'll just have this pizza, I'll be fine" whereas a higher goal means I refuse all unhealthy snacks available at work. I'm not gonna be disappointed if I don't achieve 40kg, a loss is a loss, but I need something high to aim for
